**üîß Event Tracking Responsibility Architecture**

## Primary Tracking Responsibilities

### 1. **MCP Server (Primary Event Collector)**
```typescript
interface MCPEventTracker {
  // Automatic tracking via MCP tool interception
  interceptMCPToolCall(toolName: string, params: any, response: any): void {
    // Track: token usage, tool calls, context actions
    // Detect: session boundaries, context rebuilding, success/failure patterns
    // Calculate: efficiency scores, iteration counts
  }

  // Session lifecycle management
  detectSessionStart(firstToolCall: MCPToolCall): SessionId;
  detectSessionEnd(inactivityTimeout: number): void;
  trackSessionProgress(outcomes: SessionOutcome[]): void;
}
```

**Why MCP Server?**
- ‚úÖ **Already intercepts all AI actions** - No additional instrumentation needed
- ‚úÖ **Token usage visibility** - Can measure actual AI effort
- ‚úÖ **Tool call patterns** - Detects context rebuilding vs. productive work
- ‚úÖ **Cross-tool coordination** - Sees the full AI workflow

### 2. **AI Agent (Self-Reporting + Intervention Requests)**
```typescript
interface AISelfTracking {
  // Explicit intervention requests (AI knows it needs help)
  requestHumanIntervention(params: {
    reason: string;
    attempts: number;
    context: string;
    urgency: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
  }): Promise<HumanResponse>;

  // Session outcome reporting (AI knows what it accomplished)
  reportSessionOutcomes(outcomes: {
    tasksCompleted: string[];
    problemsSolved: string[];
    knowledgeGained: string[];
    blockers: string[];
  }): void;

  // Complexity and effort self-assessment
  assessTaskComplexity(task: DevlogEntry): ComplexityAssessment;
}
```

**Why AI Agent Self-Reporting?**
- ‚úÖ **Knows its own goals** - Can report what it intended vs. achieved
- ‚úÖ **Recognizes when stuck** - Can proactively request help
- ‚úÖ **Understands context** - Knows why it's doing certain actions

### 3. **Human User (Intervention Event Logging)**
```typescript
interface HumanInterventionLogger {
  // Manual intervention logging (when human steps in)
  logIntervention(params: {
    trigger: 'human_initiated' | 'ai_requested' | 'error_escalation';
    interventionType: InterventionType;
    description: string;
    timeSpent: number;
    resolution: string;
  }): void;

  // Decision point tracking (when human makes choices)
  recordDecision(params: {
    decision: string;
    alternatives: string[];
    reasoning: string;
    impact: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
  }): void;
}
```

**Why Human Logging?**
- ‚úÖ **Knows intervention context** - Understands why intervention was needed
- ‚úÖ **Tracks time spent** - Can measure actual human effort
- ‚úÖ **Records decisions** - Captures reasoning for future AI learning

